                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#3r">Fol. 3r</locus>: Beginning of the hymn Ṭäbibä ṭäbiban "The Wisest among the Wisest Ones".<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 3r: ኦእግዚኦ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ጠቢበ፡ ጠቢባን፡ ከሃሊ፡ ለአለም፡ እምጥንት፡ እንተ፡ ኢተበሊ…  </q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The beginning of Text I (initially missing), has been written, in a secondary hand, in red and black, in the margins of fol. 3r (the same portion of text is written on the added fol. 2v).
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#30rb">Fol. 30rb</locus>: Excerpt from a mälkǝʾa-hymn for John the Baptist. <q xml:lang="gez"> Fol. 30rb: ሰላም፡ ለበድነ፡ ስጋከ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ዜናዊ። ምጻተ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ሰርቃዊ። እምከና[...]፡ ብዕሲት፡ ካልዕት፡ ወእመሰገርት፡ ነአዊ። ኦካሀን፡ ትምምክሀተ፡ ቤቱ፡ ለሌዊ፡ ለምንት፡ ሞትከ፡ እምይሙት፡ ዘማዊ። </q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Crudely written in green ink.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title ጠቢበ፡ ጠቢባን is crudely written on the front cover with yellow paint and on fol. 1r. (here written twice in blue and black pen).&#xD;
- The first five lines of fol. 3ra are framed in a square, apparently indicating that it is repeated in fol. 2vb. &#xD;
- First nine lines of Text III-2 are written on fol. 30ra.&#xD;
- Hardly readable note in pencil in which a date is partly visible: fol. 32v: &#xD;
- Writing excercises on fol. 32v.&#xD;
- Pen trials: fols.1v, 4rb.</item>
                     </list>
